This is a simulator for the Intel Intellec MDS-800 system with
64K RAM and an iSBC-202 double density diskette controller.

The front panel picture (conf/intelmds.jpg) comes from the front page
of https://www.facebook.com/groups/IntellecMDS .

The CP/M disk image was downloaded from
https://www.nj7p.info/Computers/Old%20Software/software.html .


The cpmtools disk definition for CP/M 2.2 disks is:

diskdef mds-800
  seclen 128
  tracks 77
  sectrk 52
  blocksize 2048
  maxdir 128
  skew 0
  boottrk 2
  os 2.2
end

To create a disk image for the machine:

dd if=/dev/zero of=name.dsk bs=128 count=4004
mkfs.cpm -f mds-800 name.dsk
